label: Abnormal CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cell proportion
description: A deviation from the normal proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.

label: Abnormal helper T cell proportion
description: Abnormal proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of circulating T-helper cells

label: Abnormal plasmablast proportion
description: A deviation from the normal proportion of plasmablasts in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Plasmablasts are antibody-secreting cells that originate after infection or vaccination.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive helper T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of circulating CD4-positive helper T cells relative to total T cell count.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive T cells
description: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive T cells
description: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD4+ T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4+ central memory cells
description: An abnormal proportion of central memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are located in the secondary lymphoid organs. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L+/CD45RA- phenotype.
syn: Abnormal proportion of central memory CD4+, alpha-beta T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD4+ effector memory cells
description: An abnormal proportion of effector memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are short-lived cells that migrate to the site of an infection and attempt to eliminate the pathogen. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L-/CD45RA phenotype.
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive effector memory cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive T cells
description: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive T cells
description: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD8 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD8+ T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with memory phenotype is CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.
syn: Abnormal proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells, terminally differentiated

label: Abnormal proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Abnormal proportion of class-switched memory B cells
description: A deviation of the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM-/IgD-) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA.

label: Abnormal proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: abnormal proportion of exhausted T cell relative to T cell in blood
description: An abnormally elevated proportion of exhausted T cells (Tex) among circulating T cells. T cell exhaustion is a distinct differentiation state that can be distinguished from naive, effector, and memory T cells. Compared to effector (TE) and memory (TMEM) T cells, exhausted T cells (TEX) display impaired effector functions (e.g., rapid production of effector cytokines, cytotoxicity). TEX have limited proliferative potential, especially compared to some subsets of TMEM and naive T cells.

label: abnormal proportion of exhausted T cell relative to T cell in blood
description: A deviation from the normal proportion of exhausted T cell relative to T cell in the blood.

label: Abnormal proportion of immature B cells
description: A deviation from normal proportion immature B cells (CD19+/ CD21low) in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Immature B cells (IgM+) are still in final stages of development within the bone marrow. Naive B cells are those which have left the bone marrow, before they bind to the antigen for which they're specific (IgM+/IgD+).
syn: Abnormal proportion of CD19+/CD21low B cells

label: Abnormal proportion of marginal zone B cells
description: A deviation of the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of memory B cells
description: A deviation of the normal proportion of memory B cells in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Memory B cells develop from naive B cells. Upon antigen rechallenge, memory B cells rapidly expand and differentiate into plasma cells under the cognate control of memory Th cells (Phase IV).

label: Abnormal proportion of memory T cells
description: An abnormal proportion of memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. Memory T cells have previously encountered and responded to their cognate antigen and upon a repeated encounter with the antigen can mount a faster and stronger response.

label: Abnormal proportion of naive B cells
description: A deviation in the normal proportion of naive B cells (CD19+/CD27-/IgD+/IgM+) relative to the total number of B cells. Naive B cells represent one of the subtypes of B cells in the peripheral blood, and are B cells that have not been exposed to antigen.

label: Abnormal proportion of naive CD4 T cells
description: Any abnormality in the proportion of naive CD4 T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Abnormal proportion of naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of naive CD4 T cells

syn: Abnormal proportion of naive thymus-derived, alpha-beta T cells

label: Abnormal proportion of transitional B cells

B cells originate from precursors in the bone marrow, and the first cells which migrate to the peripheral blood have been classified as transitional B cells.

label: Abnormal proportion of unswitched memory B cells

syn: Abnormal proportion of non-class-switched memory B cells

label: Increased helper T cell proportion
description: Increased proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased helper T cell proportion
description: Increased proportion of helper T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of CD4-positive T cells
description: An elevation in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4-positive T cells
description: An elevation in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of CD4+ T cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4-positive T cells
description: An elevation in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of CD4-positive T cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
description: An abnormally elevated proportion of CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype of CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Increased proportion of CD4+ central memory cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of central memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are located in the secondary lymphoid organs. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L+/CD45RA- phenotype.
syn: Increased proportion of central memory CD4+, alpha-beta T cell

label: Increased proportion of CD4+ central memory cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of central memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are located in the secondary lymphoid organs. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L+/CD45RA- phenotype.
syn: Elevated proportion of CD4+ central memory cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4+ central memory cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of central memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are located in the secondary lymphoid organs. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L+/CD45RA- phenotype.
syn: Elevated proportion central memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.
syn: Increased proportion of CD4+CD25+ Treg cells

label: Increased proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells in circulation, relative to another population of cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of CD4+CD25+ regulatory T cells

label: Increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells
description: An abnormally elevated proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label: Increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta TEMRA T cells
description: An increased proportion of CD8-positive, alpha-beta effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.
syn: Increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells, terminally differentiated

label: Increased proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
description: An increased proportion of central memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of class-switched memory B cells
description: An increase in the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA.

label: Increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells
description: An increased proportion of effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

label: Increased proportion of exhausted T cells
description: An abnormally elevated proportion of exhausted T cells (Tex) among circulating T cells. T cell exhaustion is a distinct differentiation state that can be distinguished from naive, effector, and memory T cells. Compared to effector (TE) and memory (TMEM) T cells, exhausted T cells (TEX) display impaired effector functions (e.g., rapid production of effector cytokines, cytotoxicity). TEX have limited proliferative potential, especially compared to some subsets of TMEM and naive T cells.

label: Increased proportion of exhausted T cells
description: A deviation from the normal proportion of exhausted T cell relative to T cell in the blood.

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of gammadelta T cells

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T lymphocytes

label: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of gamma-delta T cells

label: Increased proportion of immature B cells
description: An elevation in the proportion above normal of immature B cells (CD19+/ CD21low) in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Immature B cells (IgM+) are still in final stages of development within the bone marrow. Naive B cells are those which have left the bone marrow, before they bind to the antigen for which they're specific (IgM+/IgD+).
syn: Increased proportion of CD19+/CD21low B cells

label: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T-lymphocytes

label: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T-cells

label: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delat T lymphocytes

label: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
description: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells

label: Increased proportion of marginal zone B cells
description: An elevation in the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells.

label: Increased proportion of memory B cells
description: An elevation in the proportion of memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. Memory B cells develop from naive B cells. Upon antigen rechallenge, memory B cells rapidly expand and differentiate into plasma cells under the cognate control of memory Th cells (Phase IV).

label: Increased proportion of memory T cells
description: An abnormally elevated proportion of memory T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood.

label: Increased proportion of naive B cells
description: An elevation above the normal proportion of naive B cells (CD19+/CD27-/IgD+/IgM+) relative to total number of B cells. Naive B cells represent one of the subtypes of B cells in the peripheral blood, and are B cells that have not been exposed to antigen.

label: Increased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
syn: Increased proportion of naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cells

label: Increased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
Increased proportion of naive CD4 T cells
syn: Elevated proportion of naive CD4 T cells

label: Increased proportion of naive T cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of naive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Increased proportion of naive thymus-derived, alpha-beta T cells

label: Increased proportion of naive T cells
description: An abnormally increased proportion of naive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of naive T cells

label: Increased proportion of plasmablasts
description: An elevation above the normal proportion of plasmablasts in circulation relative to total number of B cells.

label: Increased proportion of transitional B cells
description: An elevation in the normal proportion of transitional B cells (CD19+/CD38high/IgMhigh) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. B cells originate from precursors in the bone marrow, and the first cells which migrate to the peripheral blood have been classified as transitional B cells.

label: Increased proportion of unswitched memory B cells
description: An increase above the normal proportion of non-class-switched memory B cells relative to the total number of B cells.
syn: Increased proportion of non-class-switched memory B cells

label: Increased proportion of unswitched memory B cells
description: An increase above the normal proportion of non-class-switched memory B cells relative to the total number of B cells.
syn: Elevated proportion of unswitched memory B cells

label: Reduced proportion of CD4+ effector memory T cells
description: An abnormally decreased proportion of effector memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are short-lived cells that migrate to the site of an infection and attempt to eliminate the pathogen. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L-/CD45RA phenotype.
syn: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive effector memory T cells

label: Reduced proportion of CD4+ effector memory T cells
description: An abnormally decreased proportion of effector memory CD4+ T cells. These are memory cells that are short-lived cells that migrate to the site of an infection and attempt to eliminate the pathogen. These cells may have a CD3/CD4/CD62L-/CD45RA phenotype.
syn: Decreased proportion of CD4+ effector memory T cells
